Description: SVU goes after Social Services after a pattern of falsified reports leads to the death of a young girl, but Benson is receiving a lot of political pressure to let it go and not open up a can of worms.

Title: Community Policing
Description: Police officers kill an innocent, unarmed black man whose description resembled a rape suspect. The case soon escalates into a public circus, with the police taking sides against A.D.A. Barba, who is feeling political pressure to indict.

Title: Maternal Instincts
Description: Rollins is placed in a no-win situation when her sister becomes a key figure in a complex case involving a rape, a drugging, and a valuable stolen flute. Meanwhile, the son of deputy chief Dodds begins working at SVU.

Title: Patrimonial Burden
Description: A reality TV family secrets begin to spill when their young teenage daughter learns she's pregnant.

Title: Melancholy Pursuit
Description: Noah gives Olivia a scare. The team catches a tough case and has to backtrack DNA from a prolific philanderer. Dodds is having difficulty with the job.

Title: Depravity Standard
Description: In trying a prior case the team runs into many obstacles, including recalcitrant witnesses and an overreaching volunteer cop. Carisi job-shadows Barba and Rollins runs into problems at the hospital.

Title: Catfishing Teacher
Description: While trying to locate a teacher who may have kidnapped a 15-year-old boy for a romantic weekend, the team discovers that the boy's kidnapping may be part of an even more sinister plot involving a coach.

Title: Townhouse Incident
Description: Benson winds up stuck in the middle of a hostage situation after her babysitter tells her that something suspicious is happening at the home of another family she works for.

Title: A Misunderstanding
Description: A high school rape accusation turns into a complicated "he said, she said" without a conclusive or satisfactory resolution of what--if anything--has taken place.

Title: Forty-One Witnesses
Description: A woman is sexually assaulted by a group of teens outside of an apartment building. SVU tries to build a case against her aggressors, but none of the the dozens of potential witnesses who saw the attack are willing to come forward.

Title: Nationwide Manhunt
Description: Two notorious killers from SVU and Chicago officer Erin Lindsey's past, Greg Yates and Dr. Carl Rudnick, escape from prison, prompting a massive manhunt.

Title: Collateral Damages
Description: A disgraced ex-boxer makes a deal to take down a group of child pornography distributors, but SVU is surprised when their busts include a deputy police commissioner.

Title: Star-Struck Victims
Description: Rollins takes matters into her own hands when Barba is forced to drop rape charges against a popular actor due to lack of evidence.

Title: Manhattan Transfer
Description: While SVU investigates a pair of vice cops found in the middle of an underage prostitution sting involving high-ranking public officials, the team discovers that a priest may be involved in a high school sex trafficking ring.

Title: Unholiest Alliance
Description: While Benson is removed from her job at SVU, the rest of the team tries to figure out who is responsible for the underage sex trafficking ring: the Catholic Church or a group of vice cops claiming to take their instructions from Ed Tucker.

Title: Sheltered Outcasts
Description: Carisi goes undercover at a homeless shelter to find out if a resident is the suspect in a series of neighborhood rapes.

Title: Fashionable Crimes
Description: A fashion photographer is accused of raping a model during a shoot, but his much more successful older designer brother tries to make the case go away.

Title: Assaulting Reality
Description: During a live broadcast, a dating reality show contestant claims she was raped by another contestant. SVU investigates, but soon learns that the show's producers are more interested in creating a successful storyline than actual justice.

Title: Intersecting Lives
Description: A corrections officer is arrested for sexually assaulting female inmates, leading his supportive union to go after Barba and SVU.

Title: Heartfelt Passages
Description: The case against corrections officer Gary Munson continues, Barba continues to receive death threats, and Dodds winds up in a hostage situation with the accused in Munson's home.

Title: Terrorized
Description: While identifying a young boy left alone in Central Park, SVU uncovers a possible terrorist plot that leads to several casualties. The DA needs a slam-dunk conviction, but the defendant's history as an abuse victim complicates matters.

Title: Making a Rapist
Description: A man convicted of rape is exonerated and released 16 years later. However, on the night of his release, the daughter of the woman he was convicted of raping is also raped and murdered, and he is SVU's prime suspect.

Title: Imposter
Description: SVU chooses to pursue a risky "rape by fraud" case involving a con artist who poses as a college admissions director to have sex with the mothers of prospective students.

Title: Heightened Emotions
Description: An aspiring Olympic athlete claims she is a rape victim, but the publicity surrounding the case could threaten her Olympic future, and reveal some shocking details about her sordid personal life.

Title: Rape Interrupted
Description: Olivia discovers that a young man facing rape charges is the son of her first police partner, who comes to her asking to cash in on an a favor that she owes him.

Title: Broken Rhymes
Description: A rising hip-hop star is a suspect in a brutal transgender beating, but his alibi might be as shocking as the crime itself.

Title: Next Chapter
Description: A woman is sexually assaulted by a masked man, but she believes the rapist is the same man who went to jail for stalking her. Meanwhile, Tucker contemplates retirement and a future with Benson.

Title: Chasing Theo
Description: SVU is on the lookout for a missing 6-year-old boy, but also discovers that the victim has a very dysfunctional home life and that the kidnappers may have actually had the boy's best interests in mind.

Title: Decline and Fall
Description: A bartender says she was raped after a birthday party for a notorious philandering businessman. The man's grandson soon claims that he had consensual sex with the woman, but the investigation later reveals a second familial match.

Title: Motherly Love
Description: A teenage boy uses a rifle to save his mother from her attacker, only to learn the target was someone he knows.

Title: Great Expectations
Description: SVU investigates the players of a youth hockey league after a locker room hazing incident.

Title: No Surrender
Description: Fin returns to his military roots when a fellow Army ranger attempts to recover from a sexual assault.

Title: Genes
Description: A suspect claims his genetics make him commit rape.

Title: Net Worth
Description: An investment banker accuses her client of rape.

Title: Know It All
Description: The suspect in a rape and murder investigation threatens to reveal the secrets of those working the case.

Title: The Newsroom
Description: Benson and Barba ask witnesses to risk their jobs when a news anchor makes a rape accusation against her boss on the air.

Title: Real Fake News
Description: A congressman asks SVU for help when he's accused of soliciting underage girls, but the investigation uncovers a sex trafficking ring.

Title: Spellbound
Description: A spiritual healer is accused of using hypnosis to sexually assault a client.

Title: Conversion
Description: Barba must argue that the First Amendment does not give a person the right to break the law when a woman is raped by a member of her church group.

Title: American Dream
Description: The daughter of a Muslim family is killed in a hate crime against them; Barba is forced to drop charges against a suspect when a witness is deported; tensions rise between communities on both sides of the case.

Title: Sanctuary
Description: Benson and Barba are caught between two families seeking justice for their loved ones in a hate crime; Benson takes desperate measures to make an arrest as public protests turn violent.

Title: Gone Fishin'
Description: Fin catches a fugitive rapist in Havana, but Barba's case is jeopardized by a political tug-of-war.

Title: Mood
Description: The bizarre details of a woman's rape put the SVU at odds when Rollins and Carisi think her story is fabricated. Meanwhile, Benson goes on the offensive when her personal life is scrutinized.

Title: Contrapasso
Description: Rollins and Carisi uncover 3 female suspects in the castration of a man who was left for dead. Langan has devastating news for Benson.

Title: No Good Reason
Description: A teenager disappears after schoolmates make her the subject of a vicious cyberbullying attack.

Title: Complicated
Description: A young woman is found wandering alone in Central Park resulting in the reopening of a 10 year old case, while Olivia Benson and Sheila Porter go to family court regarding Noah.

Title: Unintended Consequences
Description: When a teenaged girl is found dead, Rollins goes undercover at a high-end rehab center where she was last seen alive. Meanwhile, Benson tries to overcome her doubts about Sheila.

Title: Something Happened
Description: Benson must disclose the secrets of her past to help a rape victim recall the details of one terrible, traumatic night.

Title: Intent
Description: The cops get tangled in an elaborate online hoax that leads to the rape of a popular social media star. Meanwhile, Benson sets firm ground rules with Sheila.

Title: Gone Baby Gone
Description: Emotions run high as the SVU squad searches frantically for Benson's missing son.

Title: Pathological
Description: When the SVU investigates a case involving two students in a special needs school, Rollins discovers that one child's medical issues stem from a surprising source.

Title: Flight Risk
Description: When an airline pilot accuses her captain of sexual assault, Barba convenes a grand jury to determine their employer's complicity in the crime. Meanwhile, Fin takes steps to ensure Benson is protected at work.

Title: Info Wars
Description: After a female pundit is assaulted during a protest, Benson and Barba struggle to put their political beliefs aside in order to help bring the attacker to justice.

Title: The Undiscovered Country
Description: When an infant goes missing, detectives take sides in the family's right-to-die court case. Meanwhile, Barba's interference in the case puts the whole DA's office in jeopardy.

Title: Chasing Demons
Description: A doctor who was arrested for sexually abusing his patients is set free due to Cassidy's testimony which results in a mistrial.

Title: In Loco Parentis
Description: Carisi's niece reports a classmate's sexual assault; Stone discovers that there aren't any perfect witnesses when it comes to sex crimes.

Title: Dare
Description: A girl's death becomes a criminal case when a surgeon harvests her organs without parental consent.

Title: Send in the Clowns
Description: The cops search for a masked man when a student vanishes during a field trip to New York City.

Title: Service
Description: The SVU must break through military red tape when a soldier is suspected of sexual assault.

Title: Sunk Cost Fallacy
Description: Benson crosses paths with Alexandra Cabot while searching for an abducted woman and her daughter.

Title: The Book of Esther
Description: Rollins races to rescue a girl being held captive by her father.

Title: Guardian
Description: Fin investigates a man's claim that his sister was gang raped.

Title: Mama
Description: An Alzheimer's patient claims to have been raped; Fin receives his sergeant orders.

Title: Remember Me
Description: When a young woman takes a man hostage, Benson puts herself at risk to defuse the situation; SVU discovers the reason for the abduction.

Title: Remember Me Too
Description: Benson's suspicions about a kidnapping victim uncover a criminal network determined to silence anyone who gets in their way.

Title: Man Up
Description: A teenager refuses to name his attacker; Benson and Rollins reveal major life changes.

Title: Man Down
Description: In the conclusion to the season premiere, ADA Stone blames himself for the shocking verdict in Sam's case, and before Benson can offer help, Sam makes a tragic decision.

Title: Zero Tolerance
Description: After the rescue of a young girl from a sex trafficker, Benson and Stone must take drastic measures to reunite her with her mother. Meanwhile, Rollins decides to give her rocky relationship another chance.

Title: Revenge
Description: As a string of break-in assaults grows more violent, the cops investigate an online incel group to identify a suspect.

Title: Accredo
Description: A member of a women's empowerment group is found murdered, leading the cops to the group's charismatic male leader. Meanwhile, Rollins keeps her pregnancy under wraps to avoid going on desk duty.

Title: Exile
Description: A young woman wakes up in the hospital with no memory of her assault, and Carisi's investigation stalls when she disappears.

Title: Caretaker
Description: The cops wrestle with an unthinkable crime when a family is murdered in their sleep.

Title: Hell's Kitchen
Description: A waitress from a trendy New York restaurant is sexually assaulted at an after-hours VIP party.

Title: Mea Culpa
Description: Stone asks Benson to investigate a sexual assault from his past that he feels guilt and uncertainty about; Rollins considers a proposal from Al.

Title: Alta Kockers
Description: The investigation into a promising new author's death leads to a decades-old secret kept between two reclusive brothers.

Title: Plastic
Description: A woman accuses a celebrity plastic surgeon (guest star Mark Feuerstein) and his girlfriend of rape.

Title: Dear Ben
Description: A serial rapist strikes again after two decades of silence, and SVU is determined to uncover the elusive criminal and bring justice to his many victims. Stone discovers that his father worked on the case before it went cold.

Title: A Story of More Woe
Description: Benson tries to help two teenage sisters whose father has been murdered. Meanwhile, Rollins reconsiders her relationship with Al before she later goes into labor.

Title: Part 33
Description: As Stone prosecutes the case of a woman who killed her abusive husband, Benson and her squad wrestle with the duty of testifying against her.

Title: Brothel
Description: Benson and the team investigate the death of a prostitute at a brothel. They wonder if there was foul play or if this could be a case of a junkie who relapsed, turned to tricking, got depressed and committed suicide.

Title: Facing Demons
Description: Benson and the SVU investigate the death of a man they believe to be a pedophile. When they dig deeper, they realize things are not what they seem and that the case actually hits really close to home.

Title: Missing
Description: The SVU squad pursues a suspect after a child is found in the trunk of an abandoned car.

Title: Blackout
Description: When defense attorney Nikki Staines is raped after a police charity event, Benson reluctantly looks to her own for a suspect.

Title: Dearly Beloved
Description: The SVU investigates a he-said, she-said case when a woman crashes a wedding to accuse her therapist of sexual assault.

Title: The Good Girl
Description: Benson and the team work to uncover a pregnant teenager's secret when she refuses to name the baby's father.

Title: Exchange
Description: Benson helps a teenaged foreign exchange student after she's assaulted by a cab driver.

Title: Diss
Description: When a pop star is assaulted in her home, the SVU investigates the public feud between her rapper husband and a competing record artist. Meanwhile, Fin's family ties to a suspect takes him off the case.

Title: Assumptions
Description: After a Muslim woman is assaulted inside of a synagogue, SVU searches for two suspects that were spotted fleeing the scene of the crime.

Title: End Game
Description: Lt. Benson suspects Rob Miller is behind the mysterious death of a girl found dead in the Hudson River but can't prove it. Despite having only circumstantial evidence ADA Stone takes the case to court before Miller can destroy more lives.

Title: I'm Going To Make You a Star
Description: When an actress accuses a high-powered media mogul of attempted rape, Benson finds herself in a high-stakes game of cat and mouse. Changes in the squad room put Carisi between a rock and a hard place.

Title: The Darkest Journey Home
Description: Benson works with a young woman to help her remember details and suspects in her rape. In order to learn a new witness interview technique, Rollins and Fin have to experience it for themselves.

Title: Down Low in Hell's Kitchen
Description: A serial predator targeting men in gay bars proves difficult to catch, until a celebrity comes forward with his story.

Title: The Burden of Our Choices
Description: Rollins clashes with the parents of a teenaged runaway. The squad comes together for a special event.

Title: At Midnight in Manhattan
Description: The detectives are spread thin when three major cases come in at Midnight. Amanda and Carisi argue over an arrest.

Title: Murdered at a Bad Address
Description: The case of a teenage girl assaulted in the projects leads to a startling discovery; Benson puts her trust in someone from her past.

Title: Counselor, It's Chinatown
Description: The SVU squad joins an undercover task force to bust a human trafficking ring.

Title: We Dream of Machine Elves
Description: Rollins goes undercover to find a suspect who is drugging and assaulting tourists, while Benson helps the victims sort out their memories from their hallucinations.

Title: Can't Be Held Accountable
Description: A former detective asks the SVU for help when he suspects his two young daughters are being groomed by the influential predatory owner of a modeling agency for teenage girls and his equally predatory female assistant.

Title: Must Be Held Accountable
Description: A desperate father takes matters into his own hands in the case against his daughter's rapist.

Title: She Paints for Vengeance
Description: After a sexual assault investigation is stalled for months, a woman puts her accusations against a popular athlete on a billboard.

Title: The Longest Night of Rain
Description: Benson investigates a police officer's accusations of sexual assault. Captain Tucker's retirement party ends in tragedy.

Title: Redemption in Her Corner
Description: Kat steps over the line when she suspects a trainer at her boxing gym is taking advantage of his students.

Title: I Deserve Some Loving Too
Description: Rollins goes undercover to root out a government worker withholding green cards in exchange for sex.

Title: Swimming with the Sharks
Description: A woman accuses her business partner of rape, which leads to an investigation into her company's practices.

Title: Eternal Relief from Pain
Description: Rollins' sister stirs up trouble and a possible SVU investigation when she reports a doctor who trades prescription painkillers for sex.

Title: Dance, Lies and Videotape
Description: An ingénue ballerina discovers she's been secretly videotaped for a pornographic website.

Title: Garland's Baptism by Fire
Description: Garland must put friendship aside when a pastor at his church is arrested.

Title: Solving for the Unknowns
Description: The SVU struggles to find a serial predator who uses a date rape drug that leaves no evidence behind. Rollins receives some good news.

Title: The Things We Have to Lose
Description: As Carisi begins the long-anticipated trial of Sir Toby Moore, the SVU faces setbacks in several other cases.

Title: Guardians and Gladiators
Description: When the squad tries to solve an assault in Central Park, they are hampered by their own blind spots and a community that is losing trust in the police.

Title: Ballad of Dwight and Irena
Description: Rollins and Tamin respond to a dangerous domestic violence call, while Fin gives his deposition in the lawsuit against him.

Title: Remember Me in Quarantine
Description: The SVU questions a group of college roommates when one of them, an Italian exchange student, goes missing during COVID-19 lockdown.

Title: Sightless in a Savage Land
Description: While the squad spends New Year's Eve tracking down an Amber Alert ADA Carisi and Counselor Barba square off in an emotional courtroom battle.

Title: Turn Me on Take Me Private
Description: The SVU investigates when a role-play session on a camming website turns violent after one user decides to meet his idol in person.

Title: The Long Arm of the Witness
Description: Carisi takes on a powerful judge when he inexplicably dismisses the rape case of a university student.

Title: Hunt, Trap, Rape, and Release
Description: Benson teams up with Lt. Barek and the Bronx SVU to track down a serial rapist with victims in both boroughs.

Title: The Only Way Out Is Through
Description: Benson helps two sisters get closure from a harrowing childhood assault; Kat's cousin reaches out for help.

Title: Return of the Prodigal Son
Description: The squad rallies around Det. Stabler to find the suspect behind a threat to his family.

Title: Welcome to the Pedo Motel
Description: The SVU must contend with an angry neighborhood watch group when a girl goes missing near a building that houses several sex offenders.

Title: Our Words Will Not Be Heard
Description: A high-profile activist suspects her sister has been kidnapped by a hate group; Garland & Benson push for change with NYPD brass; Kat gets some good news.

Title: In the Year We All Fell Down
Description: Benson walks into a hostage situation at a neighborhood restaurant. Rollins tries to help her father after he's hospitalized.

Title: Trick-Rolled at the Moulin
Description: The SVU search for three women suspected of drugging and robbing wealthy men. The case leads to personal connections for both Benson and Kat.

Title: Post-Graduate Psychopath
Description: Rollins must revisit an old case when a child sent to juvenile detention is released after his 18th birthday.

Title: What Can Happen in the Dark
Description: Garland asks Benson to investigate an unusual domestic violence case when his neighbor is found injured.

Title: Wolves in Sheep's Clothing
Description: While Fin and Phoebe make wedding plans, Benson and Rollins try to help a homeless single mother who's being trafficked in exchange for safe housing.

Title: And the Empire Strikes Back
Description: As the investigation into a sex-for-housing scheme expands, Benson's loyalty to Garland is tested. Rollins and Carisi try to keep their witnesses on board when a powerful congressman is identified as a suspect.

Title: Never Turn Your Back on Them
Description: The search for a missing witness leads Fin and Kat down a dangerous path; Chief McGrath puts pressure on Garland and Benson to get a conviction.

Title: I Thought You Were on My Side
Description: Benson and Rollins must contend with the FBI and the Organized Crime bureau when a rape victim identifies a dangerous mobster as her assailant.

Title: One More Tale of Two Victims
Description: The SVU searches for a serial rapist who preys on mothers with young children. Benson and Fin struggle under the tightened reins of Chief McGrath.

Title: Fast Times @TheWheelhouse
Description: The SVU faces the fury of social media fans when they arrest two popular influencer brothers.

Title: The Five Hundredth Episode
Description: Amaro returns back and surprise the squad While Olivia's ex-boyfriend Burton Lowe ask SVU for help with overturning a wrongful conviction in one of Cragen's old cases.

Title: They'd Already Disappeared
Description: An investigation into missing sex workers leads SVU to a horrifying discovery.

Title: Nightmares in Drill City
Description: A fringe, possibly trafficked 17-year-old leads her rap crew to a rival's hideout under the guise of a hookup text. Homicide gets involved, and her mere involvement vs. masterminding come to question.

Title: People vs. Richard Wheatley
Description: Carisi tries Richard Wheatley for the murder of Kathy Stabler. Benson finds herself at odds with a friend when Barba agrees to take the case.

Title: Silent Night, Hateful Night
Description: The squad is called in to investigate a wave of hate crimes on Christmas Eve. Amanda catches up with an old flame.

Title: Burning with Rage Forever
Description: A boy disappears after meeting up with an online gamer. Benson suspects her son is being bullied.

Title: Tommy Baker's Hardest Fight
Description: When a popular fighter doesn't show up for the biggest bout of the year, Rollins and Velasco are drawn into a complicated web of secrets. McGrath confides in Benson.

Title: If I Knew Then What I Know Now
Description: A young woman learning about her birth parents asks Benson for help. Carisi and Rollins weigh the risks of publicly disclosing their relationship.

Title: Video Killed the Radio Star
Description: Benson investigates allegations against a popular radio personality. Rollins goes undercover when a shocking confession leads to another crime.

Title: Promising Young Gentlemen
Description: Carisi's niece helps a friend report a sexual assault; Benson investigates a college's secret society that preys on female students.

Title: Sorry If It Got Weird for You
Description: The creator of a dating app is accused of using it to rape women; Velasco's experience as an SVU detective is put on trial.

Title: Once Upon a Time in El Barrio
Description: Velasco asks Benson for help finding three girls who were trafficked from his hometown to New York City.

Title: Eighteen Wheels a Predator
Description: Rollins and Fin investigate an assault in Kentucky that has striking similarities to that of a victim found in Central Park; Benson receives intel that turns the case upside down.

Title: Tangled Strands of Justice
Description: Garland asks Benson to reopen a missing persons case he worked as a rookie officer. A victim in one of Carisi's recent cases is arrested.

Title: Did You Believe in Miracles?
Description: When a student's school reports a girl missing, the squad must track down a trusted family friend for answers. Benson gets a Mother's Day surprise.

Title: Confess Your Sins to Be Free
Description: When the only evidence in a crime is a church confession, Carisi must find another way to prove his suspect guilty. Benson agrees to meet with an old friend seeking to make amends for past transgressions.

Title: A Final Call at Forlini's Bar
Description: The SVU provides help and protection for a longtime domestic violence victim, but when she winds up at the defendant's table in court, Rollins surprises Carisi with a formidable opponent at trial.

Title: Gimme Shelter - Part Two
Description: Benson and Stabler assist in the case of a young girl's shooting and realize it's more than a typical homicide.

Title: The One You Feed
Description: A group of teens terrorizing tourists has the SVU squad working overtime; McGrath teams them up with the Bronx gang unit to track down a crucial lead.

Title: Mirror Effect
Description: Benson tries to help a pop star in a volatile relationship; Rollins struggles with taking the stress of work home with her; Fin teaches a rookie a lesson in respecting fellow officers.

Title: The Steps We Cannot Take
Description: A home invasion and kidnapping leads the SVU to a shocking discovery. Muncy tries to fit in with the squad.

Title: Breakwater
Description: A young man asks the SVU for help when he suspects his boss is preying on his sister; Velasco tries to convince a reluctant witness to testify in court.

Title: Controlled Burn
Description: A workaholic is raped after joining her boss to a shady elite party.

Title: Dead Ball
Description: When the case against a popular sports star falls through, Benson digs into the suspect's past to uncover additional victims; Velasco is disappointed when he meets one of his heroes.

Title: A Better Person
Description: The SVU hunts for a violent suspect who killed a detective's child; Rollins ponders a potential opportunity.

Title: And a Trauma in a Pear Tree
Description: Carisi and Rollins work together on an important arraignment. Benson tries to make Noah's Christmas wish come true when a case falls in her lap.

Title: Jumped In
Description: When Benson becomes the target of a ruthless gang leader, Capt. Duarte takes the case; Fin works with the Bronx SVU to help clear its case backlog; Lt. Dixon offers to translate when a deaf student is raped.

Title: Soldier Up
Description: While Benson tries to help the gang member who attacked her, Duarte reveals a shocking piece of evidence in the case. Fin is tasked with hiring new detectives for the Bronx SVU.

Title: Blood Out
Description: As Benson and Carisi put a vengeful crime boss on trial, Fin tries to help a woman who was drugged and left for dead; Velasco takes drastic action to get information from a witness.

Title: Intersection
Description: A car accident leads the detectives on a search for an ambulance driver assaulting his charges; Fin gives Detective Bruno a tour of Manhattan SVU.

Title: Dutch Tears
Description: A recently released convict goes looking for his arresting officer, Fin Tutuola; Carisi tries to get an arrest warrant without a positive suspect ID.

Title: King of the Moon
Description: A man with dementia confesses to murder, but Benson and Carisi believe there's more to the case; when rumors swirl around the squad room, Fin presses Velasco for the truth.

Title: The Presence of Absence
Description: An internet dating site becomes the source of terror for a young widow; Muncy struggles with Velasco's absence.

Title: Lime Chaser
Description: The search for a suspect who drugs women's drinks in crowded bars leads the SVU to Muncy's brother; Churlish makes a risky move to impress Benson.

Title: Bubble Wrap
Description: A construction tycoon interferes with an SVU investigation into her family. Carisi struggles to get an indictment when the complainant backs down.

Title: Bend the Law
Description: Carisi must tread carefully when Maxwell's husband becomes a person of interest in an SVU investigation. Benson sends Velasco to take an old friend into custody.

Title: Debatable
Description: Benson tries to help a student after she's assaulted on a field trip. Fin suspects a witness in the case may not be telling the whole truth.

Title: Bad Things
Description: Benson and Carisi are baffled when a series of assaults have the same M.O. but different DNA at each crime scene. Muncy believes Elias Olsen has struck again and is determined to prove it.

Title: All Pain Is One Malady
Description: In the search for a revenge-for-hire crime ring, Benson and Stabler combine forces on a case that has now spread globally.

Title: Tunnel Blind
Description: As the squad celebrates the birth of Rollins and Carisi's child, another child goes missing in broad daylight.

Title: Truth Embargo
Description: As Benson teams up with the FBI on an unsolved case, Fin and Velasco investigate a flash mob robbery that lead to a sexual assault.

Title: The Punch List
Description: The SVU helps a man come to terms with being victimized; Benson tries to support a victim's family when tragedy strikes twice.

Title: Duty to Report
Description: When Chief McGrath's daughter discloses a sexual assault, Benson must balance the intricacies of the investigation with McGrath's impulsive actions.

Title: Zone Rouge
Description: A cryptic message sends SVU on a new track to find Maddie. Benson tries to help a federal agent when the case hits too close to home. Capt. Curry tries to make amends with Fin.

Title: Carousel
Description: The SVU must track down a mysterious suspect targeting tourists staying in hostels and race to identify one woman's attacker before she opts to go home.

Title: Probability of Doom
Description: When a woman turns her husband in for possessing child pornography, the case is complicated by a sudden death. Benson tries to reconnect with a victim she saved.

Title: Third Man Syndrome
Description: A brutal assault in the street leads Carisi to pursue hate crime charges. Benson must support a home-bound witness too scared to speak up.

Title: Children of Wolves
Description: A teenager found unconscious in the park leads to a missing persons investigation. Benson must help Noah come to terms with the past when he questions the origins of his birth.

Title: Combat Fatigue
Description: The squad is on edge as Carisi waits for a verdict in Maddie's kidnapping case. Benson tries to help the Flynn family pick up the pieces of their broken life.

Title: Prima Nocta
Description: A runaway bride calls the SVU for help on the day of her wedding. Rollins pitches in on her day off.

Title: Marauder
Description: Agent Sykes struggles to cope on the anniversary of her sister's disappearance. Benson suspects a cold case from Manhattan could help her get closure.

Title: Duty to Hope
Description: The SVU searches for a pattern assailant before his crimes escalate to murder. Fin must contend with a suspect's aggrieved son. Carisi is pressured to close the case quickly to ease public concern.

Title: Fractured
Description: The SVU investigates a brutal attack on a group of law students; Benson hopes the discovery of a hidden camera will crack the case open; Carisi's best chance at conviction is catching the defendant in a lie.

Title: Excavation
Description: Devastating repressed memories come back to a woman when she finds an old notebook in her family home; bringing charges in a decades-old crime proves even more difficult for Carisi when a powerful judge stalls the case.

Title: Divide and Conquer
Description: A couple's dinner party ends with a violent home invasion and assault by masked men; Rollins suspects the crime is linked to her Intelligence investigation of an international gang of thieves.

Title: Constricted
Description: A romantic date ends with a teenager fighting for her life in the hospital; Carisi can't help bringing the case home with him as he envisions the dangers ahead for his growing daughters.

Title: Economics of Shame
Description: When a TV reporter becomes the victim of sextortion that could ruin her career, Benson helps her take back control while Velasco goes undercover as a potential rich target.

Title: Rorschach
Description: Agent Clay consults with Benson when a woman is found gravely injured at a remote campground and the suspect could be anywhere along the Eastern Seaboard; Bruno and Silva take a chance on an odd hunch to see if it becomes a lead.

Title: Tenfold
Description: Bruno must get to the center of a victim's incomplete story to track down a serial rapist; Carisi is helpless to stop a crime he suspects is about to be committed.

Title: Cornered
Description: Carisi tries to protect two women taken hostage in a tense standoff between police and a violent thief. Benson and Rollins devise a risky plan to get everyone to safety.

Title: First Light
Description: An abhorrent web of lies and betrayal is uncovered when a woman is confronted with video of a night she can't remember. Carisi struggles to move on from his ordeal when the suspect changes his plea.

Title: Master Key
Description: When a teen from a group home goes missing, the squad must quickly determine if he ran away or was abducted. Velasco puts pressure on the system at large for letting children slip through the cracks.

Title: Deductible
Description: A young boy seeks help when his sister doesn't come home from work. Benson and Carisi suspect a woman's assault was prearranged by a third party.

Title: Calculated
Description: When a high school principal busts a student for sexting, the SVU uncovers a sinister case of distribution concerning hundreds of underage students; Silva pleads for leniency for a suspect she believes is innocent.

Title: Extinguished
Description: Velasco teams up with a community security guard eager to prove his mettle to find a suspect in the assault of two teens.

Title: The Grid Plan
Description: A Midwestern tourist is viciously attacked in Times Square; as the squad scours the area for clues, the victim takes the investigation into her own hands; a secret motive threatens to derail Carisi's case.

Title: Undertow
Description: A complicated case of sex and drug use divides the squad; Carisi must convince a jury to focus on the law and not the defendant's accusations.

Title: Let Me Bring Pardon
Description: The doctor of a comatose woman calls SVU when he discovers his patient is pregnant. Benson must convince the family to reject magical thinking and look at the facts.

Title: Accomplice Liability
Description: Carisi attempts to put aside his role as prosecutor to serve as a witness in a trial; Benson tries to help a rape survivor struggling with her recovery.

Title: The Accuser
Description: When a man is ruthlessly assaulted and burned, the SVU's investigation uncovers a decades-old secret; Bruno helps a young witness find the courage to come forward.

Title: Play with Fire Part 2
Description: SVU and 2-7 discover serial rapes and murders of marginalized women, leading Carisi and ADA Price to pursue multiple charges against a suspect.

Title: Shock Collar
Description: SVU investigates if a car theft involving a young girl in the backseat was random or a planned kidnapping.

Title: Aperture
Description: When an assault at gunpoint is witnessed through a neighboring window, the squad scrambles to locate the victim to confirm she's safe; a threat to extort the victim's family leads to a shocking suspect.

Title: Post-Rage
Description: SVU investigates a string of sexual assaults involving female psychiatrists and the squad celebrates a promotion.
